Interior Cabinet Secretary Dr Fred Matiang’i and Kisii Governor James Ongwae led Gusii elected leaders in receiving Mr Kenyatta.
State burial
Dr Matiang’i and Mr Ongwae are leading the team that is planning a State burial for the late governor.
Elected leaders from Gusii, who have been reading from different political scripts, are now united by grief.
They told the Nation that their goal is to ensure a decent send-off of their departed colleague.
Nyamira Senator Okong’o Omogeni, Woman Rep Jerusha Momanyi, Deputy Governor Amos Nyaribo, MPs Ben Momanyi (Borabu), Joash Nyamoko (North Mugirango), Vincent Kemosi (West Mugirango), Shadrack Mose (Kitutu Masaba), Jimmy Angwenyi (Kitutu Chache North) and Richard Tong’i (Nyaribari Masaba) are among the leaders who were present.
Back at Nyamira Primary School grounds, thousands of residents gathered to mourn their late governor as they waited for their leaders to jet in from Nairobi.



