They also attended an interdenominational prayer service presided over by the Seventh Day Adventist Church where the late governor was an elder.
It is in the same venue where the main burial service will be held on Thursday. Only 2,000 locals will be allowed into the venue. This is to avoid overcrowding due to Covid-19.
Nyamira municipality
Nyagarama’s remains will be interred at his Tente home which is within Nyamira municipality Thursday afternoon.
The body has been lying at Lee Funeral Home in Nairobi.
Nyagarama, 74, died at the Nairobi Hospital where he had been admitted for about a month. He succumbed to Covid-19 complications.
President Kenyatta, his deputy William Ruto and ODM party leader are among leaders expected to attend the burial.
The late Nyagarama is the fourth governor in the country to die in office since 2013.
In February 2017, then Nyeri governor Nderitu Gachagua died at the Royal Marsden Hospital in London while undergoing treatment for pancreatic cancer.
In November, 2017, then Nyeri governor Wahome Gakuru died after a road accident while heading to Nairobi.





In November 2019, Bomet Governor Joyce Laboso died. The family said she had died of cancer while undergoing treatment at Nairobi Hospital.



